narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about the novel as a form and the intricacy of Henry James's work.
This class was transformative for me in how I approach reading and writing---Professor Yeazell's comments were always incredibly on point.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would say, as a senior English major, this class is amazing and definitely worth taking. For students interested in taking this class that it is very challenging and is a lot of work. Henry James is one of the most difficult authors I have ever read. Professor Yeazell might be the most brilliant academic I have ever had the chance to take a class with. She is incredible, but also a very difficult marker. Don't expect anything to be easy.
Yes, absolutely. This was one of my favorite classes at Yale.
